## 1. Business Understanding

### 1.1 Problem Statement
Movie studios, streaming platforms, and content creators need to understand audience sentiment to make data-driven decisions about content production, marketing, and recommendations. Manual analysis of thousands of reviews is impractical and subjective. This project aims to build an automated binary sentiment classification system for IMDB movie reviews.

### 1.2 Objectives
- Develop machine learning models to classify IMDB movie reviews as positive or negative
- Compare traditional ML approaches (TF-IDF + Logistic Regression) with deep learning models (LSTM, BERT/DistilBERT)
- Achieve F1-score ≥ 0.90 on test set (industry benchmark)
- Analyze which features contribute most to sentiment prediction
- Provide interpretable results for business stakeholders

### 1.3 Success Criteria
- **Primary:** F1-score ≥ 0.90 on balanced test set
- **Secondary:** Transformer model outperforms baseline by ≥ 5% F1-score
- **Tertiary:** Model training time < 2 hours on Google Colab GPU
- **Quaternary:** Identify top 10 most predictive features

### 1.4 Business Value
- **Movie Studios:** Gauge audience reception early, adjust marketing strategies
- **Streaming Platforms:** Improve recommendation algorithms
- **Content Creators:** Understand what resonates with audiences
- **Market Research:** Analyze sentiment trends over time
- **Estimated ROI:** Automated sentiment analysis can save 100+ hours/month vs. manual review

